{
  "texts": [
    "27Dual fusion categories for Rep(D 8).",
    "The dual categories for generalized discrete gauging of Rep(D 8) can also be determined from sequential gauging starting from the obvious relation with Vec D 8 by gauging the entire D 8,Rep(D 8) = ((Vec D 8) * M(D 8,1)) op, (3.32)and the reverse gauging that returns Vec D 8 by gauging the dual maximal algebraA = (1 ⊕ η ⊕ η ′ ⊕ ηη ′ ⊕ 2V) 1 in table 2, Vec D 8 = ((Rep(D 8) * M D 8,1 (1,1)) op.",
    "(3.33)We can then go down the list of L in table 2 to determine the dual fusion category A Rep(D 8) A for each algebra A and the corresponding L, using well-known results in gauging nonanomalous abelian subgroups of finite groups [9,10,33,104].",
    "When L = D 8 (with or without JHEP03(2024)127discrete torsion), we get back Rep(D 8) as is evident from the above discussion.",
    "All other subgroups of D 8 are abelian."
  ]
}